hip1:CH0004 a owl:Class,
        owl:NamedIndividual,
        hip1:CH0004 ;
    rdfs:label "Residue of Pesticides" ;
    rdfs:subClassOf [ a owl:Restriction ;
            owl:onProperty hip1:broader ;
            owl:someValuesFrom hip1:CH ],
        [ a owl:Restriction ;
            owl:onProperty hip1:isMemberOf ;
            owl:someValuesFrom hip1:HC13 ],
        hip1:SpecificHazard ;
    skos:definition "Cadmium",
        "Cadmium is a toxic heavy metal which is widely distributed in the Earth’s crust (soil and rocks), air and water; however, human activity has greatly increased levels in environmental media relevant to population exposure. Human exposure to cadmium represents a major public health concern as it has been associated with a range of acute and long-term adverse health effects and diseases (WHO, 2019).",
        "Pesticide residue means any specified substance in food, agricultural commodities, or animal feed resulting from the use of a pesticide. The term includes any derivatives of a pesticide, such as conversion products, metabolites, reaction products, and impurities considered to be of toxicological significance (FAO and WHO, no date, 2019)." .

